<br>
The tank of our group decides to scout the next room, and BAM, hes dead. I saw him get pounced on by 5 mobs, so I decide to target his corpse and drag it to the cleric for rez. As I get close enough to drag the corpse, BAM, I get hit by the 5 mobs and die.<br>
<br>
Since I have the aa ability in which I can control my pet, my hot-key looks like this:<br>
<br>
/assist tank<br>
/pause 10<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
This hot-key setup has worked great for me . . .until now<br>
<br>
Fortunately my corpse was far enough away from that room, that my corpse was draggable. I get my rez, and now we only have around 10 minutes left to kill the 5 mobs, and still need to rez the tank.<br>
<br>
Since our tank corpse is still in the bad room of 5 mobs, we decide to let me try to pacify, and then pull the room to clear a path to the tanks corpse. I was able to pacify a few, and the puller was able to single pull a mob from that room. I press my hot-key, and my pet goes in to attack the target. The strange thing is, I don't see my pet attacking the mob we pulled, and he is taking a lot of damage.<br>
<br>
Well, it ends up that since the tank corpse was nearby, my hot key assisted the corpse which still had the mob that killed him as its target, so when I pressed my hot key, my pet assisted the dead tank.<br>
<br>
The pet went into the room with the remaining four mobs, got killed and the mobs stormed out and killed me in about 2 seconds. Then they proceeded to wipe out the rest of our group.<br>
<br>
